lookupOperator

public static Operator lookupOperator(java.lang.String s)
This is the method that should always be used to get a new operator. Most of the usual operators work here, with a few changes: for == use = for != use # for <= use [ for >= use ] for && use & for || use | This is needed because of an artifact of JMAT (on which this code is based), in which operators whose string representations "overlap" each other are not allowed. In day-to-day use this shouldn't be a problem because Evaluator substitutes operators as necessary when it sees a new equation.
